.SH "NAME"
.PP
\fIecs\fP \- add client subnet address

.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
This handler adds the EDNS0 client subnet's (RFC 7871) subnet to the current context. If none is found, nothing
is added. Other handlers, like \fIgeoip\fP or \fIacl\fP can use this data instead of the source IP address.

